Package: silvermantest
Type: Package
Title: Investigate the number of modes using the silvermantest
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Florian", family = "Schwaiger", email = "schwaige@mathematik.uni-marburg.de", role = c("aut")),
    person(given = "Hajo", family = "Holzmann", email = "holzmann@mathematik.uni-marburg.de", role = c("aut")),
    person(given = "Jens", family = "Preussner", email = "jens.preussner@mpi-bn.mpg.de", role = c("cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-1927-3458")))
Description: This package contains the silverman.test, a test concerning the number of modes of an empirical density. Furthermore functions visualizing a number of tests (silverman.plot), plotting a number of densities for given number of modes (densities.plot), calculating a critical bandwidth (h.crit) and determining the number of modes for a given (empirical) density (nr.modes) are available.
